An applicant for licensure as a diabetes educator shall:
File a written application on forms provided by the board;
Provide evidence to the board showing successful completion of one (1) of the following:
A board-approved course in diabetes education with demonstrable experience in the care of people with diabetes under supervision that meets requirements specified in administrative regulations promulgated by the board;
The credentialing program of the American Association of Diabetes Educators or the National Certification Board for Diabetes Educators; or
An equivalent credentialing program as determined by the board; and
Pay licensing amounts as promulgated by the board through administrative regulation, with the following restrictions:
Initial licensing shall not exceed one hundred dollars ($100);
Annual renewal shall not exceed one hundred dollars ($100);
Biennial renewal shall not exceed two hundred dollars ($200);
Late renewal shall not exceed one hundred fifty dollars ($150); and
The reinstatement fee shall not exceed two hundred twenty-five dollars ($225).
